article.description: Malcolm Drumwright scored 25 points -- most by any Jacksonville State player this season -- and the Gamecocks rallied to trip Austin Peay 71-68 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Drumwright helps Jacksonville State rally past Austin Peay
article.linkText: Drumwright helps Jacksonville State rally past Austin Peay
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Malcolm Drumwright scored 25 points -- most by any Jacksonville State player this season -- and the Gamecocks rallied to trip Austin Peay 71-68 on Saturday night. Erik Durham capped a long second-half comeback when he drove and scored with 29 seconds left and put the Gamecocks up 69-68, their first lead of the second half. Durham scored 11 points and Greg Tucker 13 for Jacksonville State (10-8, 3-1 Ohio Valley Conference). Norbertas Giga sank two foul shots with eight seconds left and Austin Peay missed two 3-point shots as time ran out -- the last try by John Murry rolling off the iron. Austin Peay (4-13, 0-3) is still seeking a win for interim coach Jay Bowen, who took over Thursday when 27-year coach Dave Loos stepped down for cancer treatment. Josh Robinson scored 17, Kenny Jones 15, Murry 12 and Jared Savage 10. Jacksonville State led for just 4:35 and is 3-1 in OVC for the first time since 2005-06.
